They&#8217;ve parlayed strong core businesses into unparalleled global equi=
ty portfolios.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The 2020s will be India&#8217;s decade. And unli=
ke China, which features a fierce competition at the top between Tencent an=
d Alibaba, in India, Reliance is the main game in town.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em=
 0;">Reliance Industries Ltd (&#8220;Reliance&#8221; or &#8220;RIL&#8221;) =
is like an India-focused Exxon, Dow Chemical, Walmart, AT&amp;T, and Comcas=
t all rolled into one. If it fulfills its Jio vision, it will add Shopify, =
DoorDash, Zoom, WeChat, Square, AWS, and more to that roll. Its $200 billio=
n market cap is the largest in India, where its backstory, leaders, product=
s, and dramas are well-known. But when I asked a bunch of smart non-Indian =
friends what they knew about Reliance, they replied, &#8220;Who?&#8221;&nbs=
p;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 1em 0;">I salivated. Nothing gets me jazzed like an under-discussed =
Asian tech conglomerate. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">At RIL&#8217;s helm is Mukesh Ambani,=
 one of company founder Dhirubhai Ambani&#8217;s two sons. Mukesh is the ri=
chest person in Asia and the sixth richest person in the <a href=3D"https:/=
