=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">world</a>, with a net wort=
h of $85 billion. His house is worth more than whole small cap companies.</=
p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 1em 0;">Under Dhirubhai, the company was a dominant force in domestic In=
dian business and politics for nearly thirty years. Under Mukesh, particula=
rly since the start of Coronavirus, it is making a dramatic push into the w=
estern consciousness.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">This summer, Reliance made waves by selli=
ng 33% of its Jio Platforms business for $20.4 billion to a who&#8217;s who=
 of international strategic and financial investors, from Facebook to KKR t=
o Mubadala. Over the past three weeks, Reliance has been at it again, selli=
ng stakes in its Reliance Retail business to many of Jio&#8217;s financial =
investors, with a potential Amazon investment waiting in the wings.&nbsp;</=
p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 1em 0;">It&#8217;s no surprise that the world&#8217;s largest companies,=
 investors, and sovereigns want a piece. India is the world&#8217;s most im=
portant growth story, and Reliance is its gateway.</p><p style=3D"color: #1=
